15/09/2003
BARI, Italy -- Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi met with his Albanian counterpart, Fatos Nano, on Saturday (13 September) and acknowledged there is a need for the Italian business community to invest in Albania. 
Noting the strong ties between the two countries, Berlusconi urged Italian companies to participate in the privatisation of strategic sectors in Albania. 
He added that Italy would continue to play a key role in supporting Albania on its way to European integration. 
Both officials attended the 67th session of the Del Levante Fair in Bari. 
(ATA, BBC - 13/09/03)
